
TO RUN MOBILE APP: 
$> react-native run-android

If you get an error like "unable to resolve react-redux"

check if the package.json is up to date

Solution 1:
$> npm install

Solution 2 : Delete the node_modules
$> rm -fr node_modules && npm install 

Solution 3 : Reset metro bundle cache
$> npm start --reset-cache


AFTER INITIALIZING ANDROID PROJECT:

$> npm install react-navigation
$> npm install react-native-gesture-handler react-native-reanimated

$> npm install react-redux
$> npm install redux

$> npm install react-native-svg-charts
$> npm install react-native-svg
$> npm install react-native-vector-icons


TO SEE LOGS :
$> react-native log-android
